  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nFor project specific reasons, I would like to structure my codebase as follows\r\n\r\n```\r\nroot/\r\n| contracts/\r\n| tests/\r\n| | foundry/\r\n| foundry/\r\n| | foundry.toml\r\n```\r\n\r\nCurrently my `foundry.toml` file looks like this:\r\n```\r\n[default]\r\nsrc = '../contracts'\r\nout = 'out'\r\nlibs = ['../utils/ds-test', 'node_modules']\r\ntest = '../tests/foundry'\r\nremappings=[\r\n    ...\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt is able to build the contracts in the relative src directory, but is unable to find the relative tests folder.\r\n\r\nNote: On further testing, it still actually checks if there is a local test directory.\r\n\r\nThank you!\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
